tweet: Today, I’m reflecting on all that we’ve been able to accomplish for FL families over the past year. In 2018, FL businesses created over 250,000 jobs, our tourism industry set new records & our unemployment rate fell to just 3.3 percent – the lowest in 12 years.

Florida has the best state parks in the nation. I’m encouraging all Florida residents and visitors to start the new year outside, enjoying time with family and friends at  @FLStateParks. Find out more -  https://bit.ly/2Vi7i4c
Big win from @GatorsFB today in Atlanta. Congrats to Coach Mullen and the team on a great season. Peach Bowl champs!

These projects will have a strong economic impact and will greatly benefit communities throughout our state. See what the project leaders are saying about this latest round of funding here -  http://bit.ly/2BHjmCM  https://twitter.com/SenRickScott/status/1078744722984837121 …

I am happy to award $9 million from the Florida Job Growth Grant Fund to support infrastructure, workforce training & economic development projects to continue making our state the best place in the nation to get a great job and raise a family.  http://bit.ly/2CDW6Ya

We are proud to provide $24 million in funding to small and rural communities across our state to help grow their economies so more Floridians can live the American dream. More here -  http://bit.ly/2rZxiE2
Happy that this targeted funding will grow more job opportunities for Florida families. More announcements coming soon. http://bit.ly/2QVkEof

Great news for Orlando – the Orlando area has lead the state in job creation for 44 consecutive months, creating 60,800 new private-sector jobs in the past year and 315,400 since Dec. 2010.  http://bit.ly/2CuBUbk

Today was a great day celebrating more Florida economic success at @wyndestinations in Orlando. We announced FL’s unemployment rate is at a 12-year low – 3.3 percent. Thanks to the team at Wyndham for hosting & for creating new jobs in our state. pic.twitter.com/T2NlrFMTeT

FL’s unemployment rate has fallen to 3.3% – the lowest point in 12 years & nearly 1.7 million private-sector jobs have been created since Dec. 2010. I am proud of the success that FL has had over the past 8 years, allowing so many Floridians the opportunity to live their dreams.

Widespread showers and thunderstorms in the FL Peninsula today with the potential for damaging wind gusts, hail & isolated tornadoes. Floridians & visitors should monitor local news and the weather. Be aware of conditions before traveling!
